To Captain Sweat Lodge at eramon@edu.masten.net, or anon, the real ANON exposed. Edward F****in Ramon, Mr. Anon, has his covers pulled off, and there he is, sitting crying in his bed in his hug-a-bear P.J.'s, in the back room of the 57 Windstream trailer while Mom makes (literally) the rent up front, after all, it is payday for the roughnecks. Remember how you cried eddie, how you couldn't make it with the gook broads cause they reminded you too much?<br><br>
Picture this teepee Edward Indjun, with smoke slowly drifting upto the top, among the scalps, and yours still fresh and dripping, dripping, dripping in your dreams, big brave Edmondo.  I found you, suckass, just like I told you in the bush, that day you left me to die, that some day, some way, I would find you, and yours, and you would pay.  Well Well, pay day, Edwardo, Pay day at last. And to start,I want all your computer pals to know the truth about you. About how you left me with no knee, for Charlie to take. Remember Edmondo? I never forgot. Every time Charlie fucked with me or my leg, every lance, every splint, every infection, I cursed you for leaving me alive, for leaving me in their hands.  But now, I curse you, cause I survived, and thanks to this wonderful computer sight ( sorry, I ain't too good at this, but my friend is typing it in as I speak)..I found you at last.<br><br>
I am the reason you don't sleep at night Edmondo. Only You and I only know what happened that day, way out in the bush, in Charlie's county, on that food trail,  and how you left me for Charlie to find, to save your own ass.  Well Charlie came, but I was dead, fooled them I hoped, and I made it back, couple years later. But you had transfered on, no wonder huh Ed.  Well, payback time is here, on this site, for a start. And I got you now, Captain Nobody.  I am the dream master of your nightmares, Ramon, and what you have suffered for 35 years is nothing to what is coming. Call in your cyber pals, they can't help you.  They sure as shit helped me, to find you.  Now, less than 1000 miles away, I am coming, Ed, coming for my due....<br><br>
You left me to die, brave computer writer, what will you say when I knock on your door?, or along side your head?  It is payback time Edmondo sweetheart, and I want to thank all your itsy bitsy computer geek pals, for the neon sign pointing at you.  I might have missed it, but now I am on my way.......
